statement.tex:
\text{Find an anti derivative (or integral) of the}\\
	\text{following function by the method of inspection.}\\

	 \sin 2x - 4 \, e^{3x}

step.reason:
\text{Other than Chain Rule we have used the fact }\\
\text{that }\dfrac{d \left(\cos \theta \right)}{d\theta} = -\sin \theta \text{ and }\dfrac{d \left(e^{\theta}\right)}{d\theta} = e^{\theta}.\text{Check}\\
\text{your calculations if got this wrong.}
